  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;24:14">A rule set is a JSON file that tells markdown-validator what to
  check in a Markdown document. It contains two sections: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;25:67">rules</codeph>,
  which defines individual checks, and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;26:48">workflows</codeph>, which chains
  rules together with conditional logic.</shortdesc>

  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="conbody:1;29:12">

    <section id="rule-set-structure" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="section:1;31:38">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="title:2;32:14">Rule set structure</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="p:1;33:10">A rule set JSON file has the following top-level structure:</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;35:39">{
  "rules": {
    "header": [ ... ],
    "body":   [ ... ]
  },
  "workflows": [ ... ]
}</codeblock>

      <dl class="- topic/dl " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dl:1;43:11">
        <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dlentry:1;44:18">
          <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dt:1;45:15"><codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;45:23">rules.header</codeph></dt>
          <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dd:1;46:15">An array of rules that check the YAML front-matter metadata at the
          top of each Markdown file. Use header rules to validate fields like
          <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:4;48:19">ms.topic</codeph>, <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:5;48:46">ms.date</codeph>,
          <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:6;49:19">title</codeph>, and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:7;49:47">description</codeph>.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dlentry:2;51:18">
          <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dt:2;52:15"><codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:8;52:23">rules.body</codeph></dt>
          <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dd:2;53:15">An array of rules that check the document content — headings, section
          structure, text patterns, paragraph length. Body rules use XPath
          expressions to target specific elements in the rendered HTML.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dlentry:3;57:18">
          <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dt:3;58:15"><codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="codeph:9;58:23">workflows</codeph></dt>
          <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-sets-overview.dita" xtrc="dd:3;59:15">An optional array of workflow definitions. Workflows chain multiple
          rules together with conditional logic ("if rule A passes, then also check
          rule B"). If you do not need conditional logic, this array can be
          empty or omitted.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
    </section>

